<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1440,587,649]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,587,613]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The atypical narrow body form, as depicted in 
<figureCitation box="[855,933,587,614]" captionStart="Figures 82–85" captionStartId="61.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-38@61.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figures 82–85. Habitus of Axina species. 82) Axina adelosa. 83) A. bella. 84) A. bifasciata. 85) A. macilenta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565013/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
, will distinguish the members of this species from congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1440,665,866]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,665,691]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[344,387,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Size</emphasis>
. Length 12.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[668,756,665,691]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[765,824,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[901,980,665,692]" captionStart="Figures 82–85" captionStartId="61.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-38@61.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figures 82–85. Habitus of Axina species. 82) Axina adelosa. 83) A. bella. 84) A. bifasciata. 85) A. macilenta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565013/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[989,1050,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium castaneous; antenna testaceous; thorax, legs, and abdomen flavotestaceous; elytra bicolorous, mostly flavotestaceous, each elytron with basal and subapical broad dark brown fascia. 
<emphasis box="[714,771,735,761]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 50/15. 
<emphasis box="[560,638,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/ PL 110/140; elytra, few asetiferous punctures concentrated in middle of disc proximal to sutural margin EL/EW 500/80. 
<emphasis box="[281,387,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[192,969,882,909]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
